     1	# eden-task-store-server
     2	
     3	Reference implementation of the EDEN task-store process. Hosts a `Store` (in-memory, SQLite, or Postgres) behind the FastAPI app from [`eden-wire`](../../packages/eden-wire/) and exposes it over the spec-chapter-07 HTTP binding.
     4	
     5	## Run
     6	
     7	```bash
     8	python -m eden_task_store_server \
     9	  --store-url sqlite:///tmp/eden.sqlite \
    10	  --experiment-id exp-1 \
    11	  --experiment-config tests/fixtures/experiment/.eden/config.yaml \
    12	  --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8080
    13	```
    14	
    15	`--store-url` accepts:
    16	
    17	- `:memory:` — in-memory `Store` (non-durable).
    18	- `sqlite:///<path>` (or a bare filesystem path) — `SqliteStore`.
    19	- `postgresql://<user>:<pw>@<host>:5432/<db>` — `PostgresStore`.
    20	
    21	The deprecated `--db-path` alias (interpreted as a SQLite path or
    22	`:memory:`) is kept for one phase; logs emit a deprecation warning
    23	when it is used.
    24	
    25	On startup the first stdout line is `EDEN_TASK_STORE_LISTENING host=<host> port=<port>` so a supervisor / test harness can read the ephemeral port (`--port 0` to bind any).
    26	
    27	## Auth
    28	
    29	`--shared-token <T>` enables the reference-only bearer-token middleware from [`spec/v0/07-wire-protocol.md`](../../../spec/v0/07-wire-protocol.md) §12. Without it, the server accepts anonymous requests.
    30	
    31	## Shutdown
    32	
    33	SIGTERM / SIGINT drain in-flight requests, then close the store.

 succeeded in 0ms:
    30	
    31	## Run locally
    32	
    33	```bash
    34	python3 -m eden_task_store_server \
    35	    --store-url sqlite:///tmp/eden.sqlite \
    36	    --experiment-id exp-1 \
    37	    --experiment-config tests/fixtures/experiment/.eden/config.yaml \
    38	    --port 0 \
    39	    --shared-token devtoken \
    40	    &
    41	
    42	# (Read EDEN_TASK_STORE_LISTENING from stdout to learn the port.)
    43	
    44	python3 -m eden_web_ui \
    45	    --task-store-url http://127.0.0.1:<port> \
    46	    --experiment-id exp-1 \
    47	    --experiment-config tests/fixtures/experiment/.eden/config.yaml \
    48	    --shared-token devtoken \
    49	    --session-secret "$(openssl rand -hex 32)" \
    50	    --artifacts-dir /tmp/eden-artifacts \
    51	    --port 0
    52	```
    53	
    54	The web-ui announces `EDEN_WEB_UI_LISTENING host=... port=...` on stdout
    55	on bind so harnesses (and the test suite) can discover the ephemeral
    56	port without scraping logs.
    57	
    58	## Auth model
    59	
    60	- The session cookie holds `{worker_id, csrf}` and is signed with
    61	  `--session-secret` via `itsdangerous`.
    62	- Cookie attributes: `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Path=/`. `Secure`
    63	  is opt-in via `--secure-cookies` (use behind TLS).
    64	- Every mutating route validates a `csrf_token` form field in
    65	  constant time. The cookie's `SameSite=Lax` is **not** treated as
    66	  sufficient on its own.
    67	- The shared bearer never reaches the browser, the rendered HTML,
    68	  any session cookie, or any structured log line.
    69	
    70	## Healthcheck
    71	
    72	`GET /healthz` returns `{"status": "ok"}` and is **unauthenticated
    73	by design** — Compose's healthcheck must work before any user
    74	signs in. The endpoint reveals only "the process is up"; it
    75	carries no secrets and exposes no experiment state.
    76	
    77	## Stranded-claim recovery
    78	
    79	Every UI claim sets `expires_at = now + --claim-ttl-seconds`
    80	(default 1 hour). The orchestrator service runs
    81	`eden_dispatch.sweep_expired_claims` once per iteration so claims
    82	abandoned by closing the tab are reclaimed automatically — no
    83	operator action required.
    84	
    85	## Planner submit flow
    86	
    87	The planner module pins three phases:
    88	
    89	1. **Phase 1 — drafting.** For every proposal: write rationale
    90	   markdown to `<artifacts-dir>/<proposal_id>.md` (atomically, via
    91	   tmp-and-rename), build a `file://` URI, then call
    92	   `store.create_proposal(state="drafting")`. Drafting proposals
    93	   are invisible to the orchestrator's dispatch path.
    94	2. **Phase 2 — ready.** Loop over the just-created proposals and
    95	   call `store.mark_proposal_ready` for each.
    96	3. **Phase 3 — submit.** `store.submit(...)` with retry-before-orphan
    97	   on transport-shaped failures (3 attempts, exponential backoff,
    98	   leveraging chapter 07 §2.4 / §8.1 idempotent resubmit). On a
    99	   definitive divergent response or after the retries are
   100	   exhausted, the orphaned-proposals error page lists the
   101	   `ready`-but-unreferenced proposal IDs for operator recovery.
   102	
   103	The narrowest unsafe window is between Phase 2 and Phase 3:
   104	proposals are `ready` but not yet referenced by a submitted plan
   105	task. We accept this for the reference impl; it applies equally
   106	to the existing scripted planner host. A spec-level fix (atomic
   107	ready-and-submit) is out of scope for chunk 1.
   108	
   109	## Implementer module (chunk 9c)
   110	

